cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper presents a neuromorphic spiking neural network that uses delay-based learning for memory and classification. This falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper focuses on a neuromorphic network. The second likely sub-category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) as the paper discusses a novel architecture for memory and classification. The third likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper presents a learning algorithm for the network. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper discusses a neural network for pattern recognition. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper presents a reconfigurable mixed signal implementation of the architecture.
